Improving the Windows Tower processes is honestly the part of my job I enjoy the most. I’ve always been passionate about studying and refining how we solve problems. A great example of this was the new build process I developed, which nearly eliminated vulnerabilities at the source. This significantly cut down the back-and-forth of tickets with the Security team, saving everyone time. I also identified and disabled unnecessary Defender components in our templates that weren't being used in our environment. This prevented a lot of unnecessary vulnerability tickets from being opened for no reason, as those components require daily updates we didn't actually need. Finding these kinds of efficiencies and making the infrastructure cleaner and more stable is what drives me, and I plan to keep looking for these optimization opportunities to help the team stay productive.
